Installation Instructions
*************************

This document describes how to install the Wurbelizer.


Basic Installation
==================

1. User install

    Set up an environment variable WURB_HOME and set it to this
    directory, then add $WURB_HOME/bin to your path.

2. System install

    Find a place on your system, to install the Wurbelizer, 
    good choices are 

       '/usr/local/share/wurbelizer' or '/usr/share/wurbelizer'

    Define a system wide environment variable WURB_HOME and set it
    to the install directory. Ensure the $WURB_HOME/bin is included
    in the users' search path.


Fedora / RHEL / CentOS:
----------------------

Edit 'os/redhat_wurbelizer.sh' and adjust the WURB_HOME path. Then
copy the shell script to the profile directory (as root)

   # cp os/redhat_wurbelizer.sh /etc/profile.d/wurbelizer.sh

Login as a regular user, you should now be able to use the wurbelizer
tools.


